Rating: 4
Absolutely delicious, although I barely followed the recipe. I was making for a crowd, so I bought several - (different colors even) halved them and laid them open on the pan. I then drizzled them with honey, sprinkled cinnamon and brown sugar (lightly) over the top, and topped each half with a bit of butter. I skipped the lemon juice, apple juice, water and ice cream -- although I did serve them with a bit of cream in each person's bowl. HUGE HIT!!!

